             and he's really    
             excited about this.

03:42.000 --> 03:43.200
            Now, if Mr. Drake   
            shows up here       

03:43.200 --> 03:45.300
    expecting a reception and   
    there isn't a reception,    

03:45.400 --> 03:46.900
              I'm gonna have egg
              all over my face. 

03:46.900 --> 03:49.000
Actually, uh, you know,         
most complexion experts         

03:49.100 --> 03:51.000
                swear by the old
                egg facial.     

03:51.000 --> 03:52.900
It tightens one's pores.        

03:54.400 --> 03:57.800
Although yours look             
pretty tight to me.             

04:00.200 --> 04:01.900
I want to talk                  
to you a minute.                

04:01.900 --> 04:05.200
Miss Howe, I think I can get    
this wedding back on track.     

04:05.300 --> 04:06.100
                      Thank God.

04:06.200 --> 04:08.200
Yeah, but I have                
one little condition.           

04:08.200 --> 04:10.500
You pull this off and you can   
have anything you want.         

04:10.600 --> 04:11.600
Really?                         

04:11.600 --> 04:13.100
                    Except that.

04:14.100 --> 04:15.900
Actually, all                   
I want to do                    

04:15.900 --> 04:18.500
is get rid of                   
these <i>stupid</i> uniforms.          

04:18.500 --> 04:20.500
          Mr. Malone, ever since
          you have worked here, 

04:20.500 --> 04:21.700
        you have done nothing   

04:21.700 --> 04:22.900
                 but whine about
                 these uniforms.

04:23.000 --> 04:24.800
         Now, I put a great deal
         of thought into them   

04:24.800 --> 04:27.100
        and I happen to think   
        they make a statement.  
Oh, yeah.                       

04:27.100 --> 04:28.800
They say I'm a lima bean.       

04:30.700 --> 04:31.600
All right. Fine, fine.          

04:31.700 --> 04:33.400
If you insist on                
keeping these uniforms,         

04:33.500 --> 04:34.700
then there'll be                
no wedding,                     

04:34.800 --> 04:35.800
no wedding reception,           

04:35.800 --> 04:38.800
and you and Mr. Drake           
can spend an intimate evening   

04:38.800 --> 04:42.100
watching 40 quarts              
of guacamole turn black.        

04:42.100 --> 04:43.800
            Fine, fine.         

04:43.800 --> 04:45.300
        Get rid of the uniforms.

04:45.300 --> 04:46.400
    Okay.                       

04:46.500 --> 04:47.500
    Woody.                      

04:47.500 --> 04:48.600
Yo.                             
    Get on the phone.           

04:48.600 --> 04:50.100
Tell the church we're running   
a little bit late.              

04:50.100 --> 04:51.700
     Cliff, see if you can      
catch up with Eddie there.      

04:51.800 --> 04:52.600
    You betcha.                 
Norm,                           

04:52.700 --> 04:54.200
      stay in the office        
      and make sure Carla       

04:54.200 --> 04:55.400
does not trash it.              
Yes, you.                       

04:55.400 --> 04:57.600
      Frasier. Go pick up       
    Carla's gown, will you?     

04:57.600 --> 04:59.400
        Right. Oh, say,         
      if anybody needs me,      

04:59.400 --> 05:01.600
         Just tell them         
  I'm at Gown-O-Rama, tra-la.   

05:05.800 --> 05:07.100
                  That was all  
                  well and good.

05:07.200 --> 05:08.400
    Thank you.                  

05:08.400 --> 05:11.000
 How do you plan on getting the 
 bride and groom back together? 

05:11.000 --> 05:12.500
 I'm going to rely on my wits.  

05:12.500 --> 05:14.600
                  Well, you're  
                  halfway there.

05:14.600 --> 05:15.800
     You better believe it.     

05:17.300 --> 05:18.200
Sam.                            

05:18.300 --> 05:19.700
 Father Berry at Carla's church 

05:19.700 --> 05:20.700
      said we gotta hurry       

05:20.700 --> 05:22.400
because he's got                
two weddings                    

05:22.400 --> 05:24.500
planned after Carla's,          
a bake sale,                    

05:24.500 --> 05:28.400
a slide show of the Knights of  
Columbus' trip to the Holy Land,

05:28.400 --> 05:30.100
and a CYO hootenanny.           

05:30.100 --> 05:31.400
            Thank you, Woody.   

05:31.400 --> 05:32.900
    Sam?                        
                Mmm?            

05:33.000 --> 05:36.900
I'm, uh... I'm thinking         
of becoming Catholic.           

05:39.500 --> 05:40.800
      We'll talk about it later.

05:42.800 --> 05:45.100
    Hey, Sammy, I got Eddie.    

05:45.100 --> 05:46.000
      Great. Where's Mama?      

05:46.000 --> 05:48.200
     I tipped the cabbie to     
     take her back to the hotel.

05:48.300 --> 05:51.200
                You already paid
                back that buck. 

05:52.400 --> 05:54.000
I'm not gonna                   
marry her, Sam.                 

05:54.000 --> 05:56.700
I mean, I can't go              
against <i>mémère's</i> wishes.        

05:56.800 --> 05:58.100
Maybe some day,                 
after Mama gets to know her     

05:58.200 --> 05:59.100
and starts to like her....      

05:59.200 --> 06:00.100
Wait, wait,                     
wait, wait, wait.               

06:00.200 --> 06:02.100
          What about the planets
          and the tea leaves?   

06:02.200 --> 06:03.600
      I mean, if you don't      
         marry her now,         

06:03.600 --> 06:05.100
      you're going to have      
    to wait till 2042.          

06:05.200 --> 06:06.300
    Sam, it's no use.           

06:06.300 --> 06:07.600
  I mean, maybe Carla's right.  

06:07.600 --> 06:09.800
      Ever since I saw her      
      on our wedding day,       

06:09.900 --> 06:11.600
we've had nothing but bad luck. 

06:11.700 --> 06:13.800
    You know, I happen          
  to think that it's bad luck   

06:13.800 --> 06:15.900
to be a jerk to the woman       
      you're in love with.      

06:16.000 --> 06:17.500
            Now, come on, Eddie.

06:17.500 --> 06:18.800
    Just talk to her.           

06:19.800 --> 06:21.600
     Okay. I guess I could      
    just talk to her.           

06:21.600 --> 06:22.700
                Great, great,   

06:22.700 --> 06:24.500
      great, great, great,      
    hold that thought.          

06:24.500 --> 06:26.100
How's it going?                 
                    Pretty good,
                    pretty good.

06:26.100 --> 06:28.300
         It better be,          
    or my butt's in a sling.    

06:28.400 --> 06:29.800
Is there room for two in there? 

06:31.700 --> 06:33.400
          Eddie's arm.          

06:33.400 --> 06:34.700
        His neck.               

06:34.800 --> 06:35.800
How's it going?                 

06:35.800 --> 06:37.000
                Oh, not too bad.

06:37.000 --> 06:38.400
         I don't think          
we've broken anything vital yet.

06:40.400 --> 06:41.400
                Eddie's foot.   

06:41.400 --> 06:42.400
    Sweetheart.                 
                Eddie's femur.  

06:42.500 --> 06:44.500
    Sit down.                   
    Hey. Stop, stop.            

06:44.600 --> 06:46.700
Would you give the guy          
a break, please?                

06:46.700 --> 06:48.000
He had to break a mirror, right?

06:48.000 --> 06:48.900
    He had to spill the salt.   

06:48.900 --> 06:51.200
             He had to thumb his
             nose to the Fates, 

06:51.300 --> 06:52.700
         and look what happened.

06:52.700 --> 06:55.000
  They turned him into a wuss.  

06:55.000 --> 06:57.600
     The important thing is     
    that the wuss came back.    

06:57.600 --> 07:00.300
      Does he have a note       
        from his mommy?         

07:00.300 --> 07:02.400
          Oh, come on,          
     just talk to the guy.      

07:02.500 --> 07:05.500
            I don't talk to     
            spineless jellyfish.

07:05.500 --> 07:08.100
All right, fine.                
I'll just, uh,                  

07:08.100 --> 07:11.300
          go out there          
     and tell him to leave.     

07:13.300 --> 07:15.500
                    Hey.        

07:16.600 --> 07:19.600
      Does he look really       
      pathetic and cute?        

07:19.600 --> 07:21.900
 Have you ever seen a puppy...  

07:21.900 --> 07:23.800
          in the rain?          

07:28.600 --> 07:30.400
            Well...             

07:30.400 --> 07:31.800
         I guess I can          

07:31.900 --> 07:33.300
     let him off the hook,      
        but first!              

07:33.300 --> 07:37.200
He has to come in here, get down
 on his knees and sweat blood.  

07:37.300 --> 07:38.700
He was hoping you'd say that.   

07:40.400 --> 07:41.300
You're smiling.                 

07:41.300 --> 07:43.000
            The wedding's on.   
Oh, yeah.                       

07:43.000 --> 07:44.500
This uniform is almost off.     

07:44.600 --> 07:47.500
Old engineer Sammy's            
got the matrimony express       

07:47.600 --> 07:49.100
right back on schedule.         

07:50.100 --> 07:51.400
      Eddie. Eddie, Eddie.      

07:51.400 --> 07:53.100
Wait a minute, man. Whoa.       

07:53.100 --> 07:54.100
                Where you going?

07:54.100 --> 07:55.500
I can't face her                
right now.                      

07:55.500 --> 07:57.400
I mean, even if I did           
change my mind                  

07:57.500 --> 07:58.900
and decide                      
to stand up to Mama,            

07:58.900 --> 08:01.300
Carla would never forgive me    
for the way I ran out.          

08:01.300 --> 08:03.000
I mean, if I went               
in there right now,             

08:03.000 --> 08:04.100
she'd tear my head off.         

08:04.200 --> 08:05.400
        Come on, Eddie.         

08:05.400 --> 08:08.600
 I think you're underestimating 
     Carla just a bit here.     

08:08.700 --> 08:10.300
What, you don't think           
she'll be mad?                  

08:10.300 --> 08:11.800
    No, I don't think           
she'll stop at your head.       

08:11.800 --> 08:12.800
SAM:                            
Norm...                         

08:12.800 --> 08:15.000
            Listen, she wants   
            to forgive you.     

08:15.100 --> 08:18.900
    All you two need is a few   
    moments together in private.

08:18.900 --> 08:20.400
Okay, but could we              
do it out here,                 

08:20.500 --> 08:22.300
where there are                 
plenty of witnesses?            

08:22.300 --> 08:23.600
                All right. Okay.

08:23.600 --> 08:24.900
Just sit down right here. Relax.

08:24.900 --> 08:27.000
If he even looks at the door,   
break his legs.                 

08:28.400 --> 08:29.700
              Sam!              

08:29.700 --> 08:31.100
